@jhlfscThe point is that attempting to exclude trans people from the LGBT community objectively harms both trans people and the LGBT community as a whole. That's why reactionaries have decided it's a good idea, and why your rationalisation really doesn't matter, except to help determine whether it comes from naivety or malice.
Also, it's not 'alleged'. Trying to get trans people excluded from the LGBT community is the explicit strategy of the far right at this point. That's why there are astroturf groups like the British 'LGB Alliance' (made up of media people, Tory politicians, and basically no LGBT people). That's why fascists were trying to get 'LGBwithoutTheT' trending a while back. 
It turns out that attempting to undermine solidarity between marginalised people who share common enemies is bad, actually.
